  328. ‌             let obj_tag = O.tag obj in
  329.              (* Lazy values are represented in three possible ways:

  331.                 1. a lazy thunk that is not yet forced has tag
  332.                    Obj.lazy_tag

  334.                 2. a lazy thunk that has just been forced has tag
  335.                    Obj.forward_tag; its first field is the forced
  336.                    result, which we can print

  338.                 3. when the GC moves a forced trunk with forward_tag,
  339.                    or when a thunk is directly created from a value,
  340.                    we get a third representation where the value is
  341.                    directly exposed, without the Obj.forward_tag
  342.                    (if its own tag is not ambiguous, that is neither
  343.                    lazy_tag nor forward_tag)

  345.                 Note that using Lazy.is_val and Lazy.force would be
  346.                 unsafe, because they use the Obj.* functions rather
  347.                 than the O.* functions of the functor argument, and
  348.                 would thus crash if called from the toplevel
  349.                 (debugger/printval instantiates Genprintval.Make with
  350.                 an Obj module talking over a socket).
  351.               *)
  352.              if obj_tag = Obj.lazy_tag then Oval_stuff "<lazy>"
  353.              else begin
  354. ‌                 let forced_obj =
  355.                    if obj_tag = Obj.forward_tag then O.field obj 0 else obj
  356.                  in
  357.                  (* calling oneself recursively on forced_obj risks
  358.                     having a false positive for cycle detection;
  359.                     indeed, in case (3) above, the value is stored
  360.                     as-is instead of being wrapped in a forward
  361.                     pointer. It means that, for (lazy "foo"), we have
  362.                       forced_obj == obj
  363.                     and it is easy to wrongly print (lazy <cycle>) in such
  364.                     a case (PR#6669).

  366.                     Unfortunately, there is a corner-case that *is*
  367.                     a real cycle: using unboxed types one can define

  369.                        type t = T : t Lazy.t -> t [@@unboxed]
  370.                        let rec x = lazy (T x)

  372.                     which creates a Forward_tagged block that points to
  373.                     itself. For this reason, we still "nest"
  374.                     (detect head cycles) on forward tags.
  375.                   *)

  407.                           | _ -> assert false end
  408.                       | None -> decl.type_params
  409.                     in
  410.                     begin
  411.                       match cd_args with
  412.                       | Cstr_tuple l ->
  413. ‌                          let ty_args =
  414.                             instantiate_types env type_params ty_list l in
  415.                           tree_of_constr_with_args (tree_of_constr env path)
  416.                             (Ident.name cd_id) false 0 depth obj
  417.                             ty_args unbx
  418.                       | Cstr_record lbls ->
  419. ‌                          let r =
  420.                             tree_of_record_fields depth
  421.                               env path type_params ty_list
  422.                               lbls 0 obj unbx
  423.                           in
  424.                           Oval_constr(tree_of_constr env path
  425.                                         (Out_name.create (Ident.name cd_id)),
  426.                                       [ r ])
  427.                     end
  428.                 | {type_kind = Type_record(lbl_list, rep)} ->
  429.                     begin match check_depth depth obj ty with
  430.                       Some x -> x
  431.                     | None ->
  432. ‌                        let pos =
  433.                           match rep with
  434.                           | Record_extension _ -> 1
  435.                           | _ -> 0
  436.                         in
  437. ‌                        let unbx =
  438.                           match rep with Record_unboxed _ -> true | _ -> false
  439.                         in
  440.                         tree_of_record_fields depth
  441.                           env path decl.type_params ty_list
  442.                           lbl_list pos obj unbx
  443.                     end
  444.                 | {type_kind = Type_open} ->
  445.                     tree_of_extension path ty_list depth obj
  446.               with
  447.                 Not_found ->                (* raised by Env.find_type *)
  448.                   Oval_stuff "<abstr>"
  449.               | Datarepr.Constr_not_found -> (* raised by find_constr_by_tag *)
  450.                   Oval_stuff "<unknown constructor>"
  451.               end
  452.           | Tvariant row ->
  453.               if O.is_block obj then
  454. ‌                let tag : int = O.obj (O.field obj 0) in
  455. ‌                let rec find = function
  456.                   | (l, f) :: fields ->
  457.                       if Btype.hash_variant l = tag then
  458.                         match row_field_repr f with
  459.                         | Rpresent(Some ty) | Reither(_,[ty],_) ->
  460.                             let args =
  461.                               nest tree_of_val (depth - 1) (O.field obj 1) ty
  462.                             in
  463.                               Oval_variant (l, Some args)
  464.                         | _ -> find fields
  465.                       else find fields
  466.                   | [] -> Oval_stuff "<variant>" in
  467.                 find (row_fields row)
  468.               else
  469. ‌                let tag : int = O.obj obj in
  470. ‌                let rec find = function
  471.                   | (l, _) :: fields ->
  472.                       if Btype.hash_variant l = tag then
  473.                         Oval_variant (l, None)
  474.                       else find fields
  475.                   | [] -> Oval_stuff "<variant>" in
  476.                 find (row_fields row)
  477.           | Tobject (_, _) ->
  478.               Oval_stuff "<obj>"
  479.           | Tsubst _ | Tfield(_, _, _, _) | Tnil | Tlink _ ->
  480.               fatal_error "Printval.outval_of_value"
  481.           | Tpoly (ty, _) ->
  482.               tree_of_val (depth - 1) obj ty
  483.           | Tpackage _ ->
  484.               Oval_stuff "<module>"
  485.         end

  487. ‌      and tree_of_record_fields depth env path type_params ty_list
  488.           lbl_list pos obj unboxed =
  489.         let rec tree_of_fields pos = function
  490.           | [] -> []
  491.           | {ld_id; ld_type} :: remainder ->
  492.               let ty_arg = instantiate_type env type_params ty_list ld_type in
  493.               let name = Ident.name ld_id in
  494.               (* PR#5722: print full module path only
  495.                  for first record field *)
  496.               let lid =
  497.                 if pos = 0 then tree_of_label env path (Out_name.create name)
  498.                 else Oide_ident (Out_name.create name)
  499.               and v =
  500.                 if unboxed then
  501.                   tree_of_val (depth - 1) obj ty_arg
  502.                 else begin
  503.                   let fld =
  504.                     if O.tag obj = O.double_array_tag then
  505.                       O.repr (O.double_field obj pos)
  506.                     else
  507.                       O.field obj pos
  508.                   in
  509.                   nest tree_of_val (depth - 1) fld ty_arg
  510.                 end
  511.               in
  512.               (lid, v) :: tree_of_fields (pos + 1) remainder
  513.         in
  514.         Oval_record (tree_of_fields pos lbl_list)

  516. ‌      and tree_of_val_list start depth obj ty_list =
  517.         let rec tree_list i = function
  518.           | [] -> []
  519.           | ty :: ty_list ->
  520.               let tree = nest tree_of_val (depth - 1) (O.field obj i) ty in
  521.               tree :: tree_list (i + 1) ty_list in
  522.       tree_list start ty_list

  524.       and tree_of_constr_with_args
  525.              tree_of_cstr cstr_name inlined start depth obj ty_args unboxed =
  526.         let lid = tree_of_cstr (Out_name.create cstr_name) in
  527.         let args =
  528.           if inlined || unboxed then
  529.             match ty_args with
  530.             | [ty] -> [ tree_of_val (depth - 1) obj ty ]
  531.             | _ -> assert false
  532.           else
  533.             tree_of_val_list start depth obj ty_args
  534.         in
  535.         Oval_constr (lid, args)

  537.     and tree_of_extension type_path ty_list depth bucket =
  538.       let slot =
  539.         if O.tag bucket <> 0 then bucket
  540.         else O.field bucket 0
  541.       in
  542.       let name = (O.obj(O.field slot 0) : string) in
  543.       try
  544.         (* Attempt to recover the constructor description for the exn
  545.            from its name *)
  546.         let lid =
  547.           try Parse.longident (Lexing.from_string name) with
  548.           (* The syntactic class for extension constructor names
  549.              is an extended form of constructor "Longident.t"s
  550.              that also includes module application (e.g [F(X).A]) *)
  551.            | Syntaxerr.Error _ | Lexer.Error _ -> raise Not_found in
  552.         let cstr = Env.find_constructor_by_name lid env in
  553.         let path =
  554.           match cstr.cstr_tag with
  555.             Cstr_extension(p, _) -> p
  556.             | _ -> raise Not_found
  557.         in
  558.         let addr = Env.find_constructor_address path env in
  559.         (* Make sure this is the right exception and not an homonym,
  560.            by evaluating the exception found and comparing with the
  561.            identifier contained in the exception bucket *)
  562.         if not (EVP.same_value slot (EVP.eval_address addr))
  563.         then raise Not_found;
  564.         let type_params =
  565.           match get_desc cstr.cstr_res with
  566.             Tconstr (_,params,_) ->
  567.              params
  568.           | _ -> assert false
  569.         in
  570.         let args = instantiate_types env type_params ty_list cstr.cstr_args in
  571.         tree_of_constr_with_args
  572.            (fun x -> Oide_ident x) name (cstr.cstr_inlined <> None)
  573.            1 depth bucket
  574.            args false
  575.       with Not_found | EVP.Error ->
  576.         match check_depth depth bucket ty with
  577.           Some x -> x
  578.         | None when Path.same type_path Predef.path_exn->
  579.             outval_of_untyped_exception bucket
  580.         | None ->
  581.             Oval_stuff "<extension>"

  583.     and instantiate_type env type_params ty_list ty =
  584.       try Ctype.apply env type_params ty ty_list
  585.       with Ctype.Cannot_apply -> abstract_type

  587.     and instantiate_types env type_params ty_list args =
  588.       List.map (instantiate_type env type_params ty_list) args

  590.     and find_printer depth env ty =
  591.       let rec find = function
  592.       | [] -> raise Not_found
  593.       | (_name, Simple (sch, printer)) :: remainder ->
  594.           if Ctype.is_moregeneral env false sch ty
  595.           then printer
  596.           else find remainder
  597.       | (_name, Generic (path, fn)) :: remainder ->
  598.           begin match get_desc (Ctype.expand_head env ty) with
  599.           | Tconstr (p, args, _) when Path.same p path ->
  600.               begin try apply_generic_printer path (fn depth) args
  601.               with exn -> (fun _obj -> out_exn path exn) end
  602.           | _ -> find remainder end in
  603.       find !printers

  605.     and apply_generic_printer path printer args =
  606.       match (printer, args) with
  607.       | (Zero fn, []) ->
  608.           (fun (obj : O.t)-> try fn obj with exn -> out_exn path exn)
  609.       | (Succ fn, arg :: args) ->
  610.           let printer = fn (fun depth obj -> tree_of_val depth obj arg) in
  611.           apply_generic_printer path printer args
  612.       | _ ->
  613.           (fun _obj ->
  614.             let printer ppf =
  615.               fprintf ppf "<internal error: incorrect arity for '%a'>"
  616.                 Printtyp.path path in
  617.             Oval_printer printer)


  620.     in nest tree_of_val max_depth obj (Ctype.correct_levels ty)

  622. end
